@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "The Browser in Web Communication";
}

<body data-topic="web-communication-browser">
<div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center">What is a Browser in Web Communication?</h1>

    <div class="beginner-note">
        <div class="beginner-note-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-globe"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="beginner-note-content">
            <h4>Think of the Browser Like a TV Remote + TV Combo</h4>
            <p><strong>Browser = Your window to the internet world</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Simple analogy:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Remote (Browser) lets you choose what to watch</li>
                <li>TV Screen (Browser) displays the show</li>
                <li>Channels (Websites) are different content sources</li>
                <li>You control everything with the remote</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>In web terms:</strong> The browser is your tool to access and interact with websites!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
        <p>A <strong>web browser</strong> is a software application that lets you access, view, and interact with websites on the internet. It's like your <strong>personal tour guide</strong> through the digital world!</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Quick Definition:</strong> A browser is <strong>your tool for surfing the web</strong> - it shows websites and lets you click around.
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Popular Browsers You Probably Use</h2>
    
    <div class="browser-gallery">
        <div class="browser-card">
            <div class="browser-icon chrome">
                <i class="fab fa-chrome"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>Google Chrome</h4>
            <p><strong>Used by:</strong> ~65% of people</p>
            <p><strong>Specialty:</strong> Speed and Google integration</p>
            <p><strong>Fun fact:</strong> Most popular browser worldwide!</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="browser-card">
            <div class="browser-icon safari">
                <i class="fab fa-safari"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>Apple Safari</h4>
            <p><strong>Used by:</strong> ~18% of people</p>
            <p><strong>Specialty:</strong> Apple device optimization</p>
            <p><strong>Fun fact:</strong> Default on all Apple devices</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="browser-card">
            <div class="browser-icon firefox">
                <i class="fab fa-firefox"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>Mozilla Firefox</h4>
            <p><strong>Used by:</strong> ~7% of people</p>
            <p><strong>Specialty:</strong> Privacy and customization</p>
            <p><strong>Fun fact:</strong> Open-source and community-driven</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="browser-card">
            <div class="browser-icon edge">
                <i class="fab fa-edge"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>Microsoft Edge</h4>
            <p><strong>Used by:</strong> ~5% of people</p>
            <p><strong>Specialty:</strong> Windows integration</p>
            <p><strong>Fun fact:</strong> Replaced Internet Explorer</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">What a Browser Actually Does - Step by Step</h2>
    
    <div class="browser-process">
        <div class="process-step">
            <div class="process-number">1</div>
            <div class="process-content">
                <h5>You Type a URL</h5>
                <p>Example: "youtube.com" in the address bar</p>
                <div class="address-bar-example">
                    <div class="address-bar">
                        <span class="lock-icon"><i class="fas fa-lock"></i></span>
                        <span class="url">https://www.youtube.com</span>
                        <span class="refresh-icon"><i class="fas fa-redo"></i></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="process-step">
            <div class="process-number">2</div>
            <div class="process-content">
                <h5>Browser Sends Request</h5>
                <p>Browser tells YouTube's server: "Please send me your homepage"</p>
                <div class="request-visual">
                    <div class="browser-icon-small">
                        <i class="fab fa-chrome"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="arrow">
                        <i class="fas fa-paper-plane"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="server-icon-small">
                        <i class="fas fa-server"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="request-text">GET / HTTP/1.1</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="process-step">
            <div class="process-number">3</div>
            <div class="process-content">
                <h5>Receives & Processes</h5>
                <p>Gets back HTML, CSS, JavaScript files and puts them together</p>
                <div class="code-preview">
                    <div class="code-tab active">HTML</div>
                    <div class="code-tab">CSS</div>
                    <div class="code-tab">JavaScript</div>
                    <div class="code-content">
                        &lt;div class="video"&gt;🎬&lt;/div&gt;<br>
                        &lt;button class="play"&gt;▶ Play&lt;/button&gt;
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="process-step">
            <div class="process-number">4</div>
            <div class="process-content">
                <h5>Displays the Page</h5>
                <p>Shows you the complete YouTube website, ready to use!</p>
                <div class="page-preview">
                    <div class="page-header">YouTube</div>
                    <div class="page-content">
                        <div class="video-thumb">📹 Recommended Video</div>
                        <div class="video-thumb">🎵 Music Video</div>
                        <div class="video-thumb">😄 Funny Cats</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Browser Parts - Your Control Panel</h2>
    
    <div class="browser-anatomy">
        <div class="anatomy-diagram">
            <div class="browser-window">
                <div class="browser-tabs">
                    <div class="tab active">YouTube - Watch videos</div>
                    <div class="tab">Google - Search</div>
                    <div class="tab">Facebook - Social</div>
                    <div class="tab new-tab">+</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="browser-nav">
                    <div class="nav-button"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i></div>
                    <div class="nav-button"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></div>
                    <div class="nav-button"><i class="fas fa-redo"></i></div>
                    <div class="address-bar-full">
                        <i class="fas fa-lock"></i>
                        https://www.youtube.com
                    </div>
                    <div class="nav-button"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></div>
                    <div class="nav-button"><i class="fas fa-ellipsis-v"></i></div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="browser-content">
                    <div class="content-area">
                        <h4>Welcome to YouTube!</h4>
                        <p>Your personalized video recommendations appear here...</p>
                        <button class="play-button"><i class="fas fa-play"></i> Play Video</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="browser-footer">
                    <div class="status">Loaded successfully</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="anatomy-explanation">
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-marker">①</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Tabs:</strong> Open multiple websites at once, like having several TV channels ready
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-marker">②</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Address Bar:</strong> Where you type website addresses (URLs)
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-marker">③</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Back/Forward:</strong> Navigate through your browsing history
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-marker">④</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Refresh:</strong> Reload the current page if something isn't working
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-marker">⑤</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Content Area:</strong> Where websites actually display
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="browser-features">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Cool Browser Features You Use Everyday</h3>
        
        <div class="features-grid">
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-bookmark"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h5>Bookmarks</h5>
                    <p>Save your favorite websites for quick access later</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-history"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h5>History</h5>
                    <p>Remember where you've been (like a browsing diary)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-download"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h5>Downloads</h5>
                    <p>Save files, images, and documents from websites</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-user-secret"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h5>Incognito Mode</h5>
                    <p>Browse privately without saving history</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-plug"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h5>Extensions</h5>
                    <p>Add extra features like ad blockers or password managers</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-memory"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <h5>Cache</h5>
                    <p>Remember website parts to load faster next time</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="interactive-activity">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-gamepad"></i> Browser Detective Activity</h3>
        <p>Look at your own browser right now and find these things:</p>
        
        <div class="activity-checklist">
            <div class="checklist-item">
                <input type="checkbox" id="check1">
                <label for="check1">Find the address bar (where the website URL is)</label>
            </div>
            <div class="checklist-item">
                <input type="checkbox" id="check2">
                <label for="check2">Count how many tabs you have open</label>
            </div>
            <div class="checklist-item">
                <input type="checkbox" id="check3">
                <label for="check3">Click the back button (or try forward)</label>
            </div>
            <div class="checklist-item">
                <input type="checkbox" id="check4">
                <label for="check4">Find the refresh/reload button</label>
            </div>
            <div class="checklist-item">
                <input type="checkbox" id="check5">
                <label for="check5">Right-click anywhere and see the menu</label>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="activity-tip">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Try pressing <kbd>Ctrl+T</kbd> (Windows) or <kbd>Cmd+T</kbd> (Mac) to open a new tab!
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Browser = Web Viewer</strong> - Your window to see websites</li>
            <li><strong>Multiple types:</strong> Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>Requests pages:</strong> Asks servers for website files</li>
            <li><strong>Assembles pages:</strong> Puts together HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
            <li><strong>Displays content:</strong> Shows you the final website</li>
            <li><strong>Has features:</strong> Tabs, bookmarks, history, extensions</li>
            <li><strong>You control it:</strong> You decide where to go and what to do</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("Server", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-outline-primary ajax-link">← What is a Server?</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("HttpPart1", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-primary ajax-link">Next: HTTP Protocol - Part 1 →</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 900px;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: var(--bs-body-bg);
    }

    h1, h2, h3, h4, h5 {
        color: var(--bs-heading-color);
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    h1 {
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--bs-primary);
        padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .beginner-note {
